SIMPLE: overween
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Overween
<hw>O`ver*ween"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[AS.
<ets>oferw⟦emac⟧nian</ets>. See <er>Over</er>, and <er>Ween</er>.]</ety>
<def>To think too highly or arrogantly; to regard one's own thinking or
conclusions too highly; hence, to be egotistic, arrogant, or rash, in
opinion; to think conceitedly; to presume.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>They that <qex>overween</qex>,⟦br⟧
And at thy growing virtues fret their spleen.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Overweener</ent>⟦br⟧
